@2
Well  your  system can crash for a number of resons,  the most common  being
inadequate power supply which is one of the main causes,  a tower especially
from  Eyetech  with a 250 watt PSU will go a long way towards  solving  that
problem,   also the large Eyetech towers will go a long way  to  being  very
compatible with any future upgrades you decide to do on your miggy,   except
for  those who want to go over to the Z4 cards and Cybervisionc64 3D graphic
cards,   then you'll have to but the specially designed Z4 tower  for  that,
but that's another matter.



A  tower  will also mean that all those unsightly wires that used  to  cover
your  computer desk like some crazy man eating vine from sci-fi  films  will
all  be trapped or tucked away inside the tower,  admittedly you'll  end  up
having to use a PC keyboard,  well, unless you spend an extra few quid on an
A4000  keyboard,   which thanks to Malc Megabite he recently  sold  me  one,
cheers Malc.



Now,  one of the necommers in The Ripper (along with myself)  is called  Ray
Hawkins (Dungeon Master)  up till recently totally rejected the idea of ever
towering  his  miggy up,  for reasons of making a bit PCish I suppose,   but
anyway,  it was only till recently that Master Craig Daines (Hercules)  from
our  ex-  diskmag The Crypt has decided to upgrade his miggy  to  the  newly
advertised  Z4  board CV63 3D graphics cards and Eyetech specially  designed
Z4 tower,  and so he decided to sell his old six-storey (a joke between Ray,
Craig  and myself about the size of the old tower)  and sell his old Eyetech
MkII  tower  to Ray H,  having bought it and thanks to Craig,  Ray  recently
said  to  me  on the phone one night that it was probably one  of  the  best
investments he had ever made for his trusty old miggy,  a big beefy PSU will
stop  or  ease the crashes which are caused by smaller PSU's,  and  with  so
much space in the tower for future upgrading og a Zip drive,  or an LS  120,
a  CD ROM rewriter etc etc he'll be well and truly sorted in that department
for the future.
