@3
Right,   this  next item is really of some importance,  it  concerns  3  new
upgrades  on the market which I think I will put under one label "Graphics",
the three items being,  the new Z4 card,  the Cybervision64 3D Graphics card
and lastly the Eyetech Z4 Towercase,  now,  although the towercase is only a
item  for  putting the other two into I think that it should be  classed  as
part of this package if your going to upgrade to a graphics card,  you  see,
as  far  as  I  know you can't use the above graphics card  without  the  Z4
board,  and one of the Z4's main funtions is to support graphics card,   and
again,  as far as I know,  the only tower available to support the other two
items  is  the  Eyetech  Z4 tower,  so yes,  these  three  items  should  be
categorized as one package.

Anyway,   the reason for typing this file and telling you about these  three
items is so as to point out the possible implications of what could possibly
turn your working miggy into a totaly knackered system.
@1
Two  of  my contact namely "Snoopy" and Craig Daines (aka Hercules from  our
days  with  The Crypt)  have both just upgraded their respective systems  to
with the above items,  now,  Snoopy followed all the technical help that was
supplied  down to the letter,  but upon bootup time he found his system  was
dead as the pervebial dodo,  diagnosis, one fucked up motherboard and WB 3.1
ROMS  I  think,  solution,  pay ourmore cash and send the cah and  his  full
system  off to Eyetech for them to install and setup everything,   which  of
course has cost him a lot of cash in the first place for the Z4 board,   the
Z4  Tower and Cybervision64 3D graphics card,  and with him having  to  send
the  whole lot off to Eyetech to get them to sort it all out it's  cost  the
poor  lad another £150 or so quid on top,  which even for us workers  is  no
joke.

Craig on the other hand had a slightly different problem but the end results
were almost the same, being the clever sod that he is (ex Crypt members will
know  of  his  computer skills)  Craig and his mate installed  all  the  new
hardware  onto  Craig's  A1200 themselves,  and  apparently  Craig's  system
booted  up  ok  and  worked for a few days,  but then disater  struck,   and
although I don't exactly know what happened,  then end result was almost the
same as Snoopy's, a knackered A1200T system.

So what do we do in order to stop or cut the risk our our machines ending up
like these two lads have done,  well I think that there are two way of doing
it,   well,   that's of course if you want to add a graphics  card  to  your
system  which  for  the less technical amongst us means  that  with  if  the
cybervision graphics card has got 4 Mb fitted to it then together with  your
standard  A1200's  2Mb of chip RAM you'll end up with 6Mb  of  chip  memory,
which we must all admit has got to be a real good added bonus,  so following
on  from  above,  what do we do to hopefully stop our systems up like  these
two lads have done,  personally I would prefer to pay an extra few quid  and
send of most of my system to Eyetech and let them do the installation,  that
way  you'll know that it's been done properly,  and no,  I'm not saying that
these  two  lads done things wrong,  it's just that the new Z4 tower  is  so
tight for space inside it that anything could have caused their problems.
